===Etymology===
Via Old French from {{L.}} ''[[coniunctio|coniūnctiō]]'', joining, from ''[[coniungere]]'', to join.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌŋkʃən|-ʌŋkʃən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#The act of joining or being joined.
#{{grammar}} A word used to join other words or phrases together into sentences. The specific conjunction used shows how the two joined parts are related.
#{{astronomy}} The alignment of two bodies in the [[solar system]] such that they have the same [[longitude]] when seen from Earth.
# {{cattag|logic}} The [[proposition]] resulting from the combination of two or more propositions using the [[∧]] (<math>\and</math>) [[operator]].

